title: General view - Queens - Northern Boulevard - Junction Boulevard (West and Southwest).

text: Northern Boulevard (foreground), at the S.W. corner of Junction Boulevard (left), showing in a set of three views, property and house of C. P. Leverich from 1873 to 1891.  Matilda Bradford was the owner in 1909. This house was demolished to make way for the extension of 94th Street. This is a set of three views. To the right of the house, in the background, in View No. 1 is seen the tower of Public School No. 15. View No. 3 shows the out buildings and the east side of Junction Boulevard (two family houses thereon). These building were demolished in October 1925. Views 1 and 3: March 1924. View 2: March 1924. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
